<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="could-modal-v">could <strong><em>modal v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kəd;kʊd/    美 /kəd;kʊd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>能；会</strong></h4>
<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>可能；大概：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The weather in Shanghai could be very cold in winter.
上海的冬季有时会很冷。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>能；可以：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you do something for me?
你能帮帮我吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You could ask your doctor for a check-up.
你可以让医生做个检查。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>能； 可以：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wish it could clear up.
天要是放晴该多好啊。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If I could have gone with you, I should have felt very glad.
要是我当时能同你们一起去，我会非常开心。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I can’t find my purse. I______ it in the supermarket yesterday, but I’m not sure.   （2018 天津）<br />
A.should leave<br />
B.must have left<br />
C.might leave<br />
D.could have left  </li>
<li>It was so noisy that we <strong><em>_</em></strong> hear ourselves speak.   （2015 浙江）<br />
A.couldn’t<br />
B.shouldn’t<br />
C.mustn’t<br />
D.needn’t  </li>
<li>It <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ be the vocabulary that caused you the problem in the exercise because you know a lot of words.  （2013 安徽）<br />
A.may <br />
B.couldn’t<br />
C.should <br />
D.needn’t  </li>
<li>— Happy birthday!
— Thank you! It’s the best present I ______ for.   （2012 江苏）<br />
A.should have wished<br />
B.must have wished<br />
C.may have wished<br />
D.could have wished  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  2. A  3. B  4. D  </p></div>